    <section id="features" class="ud-features">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-12">
            <div class="ud-section-title">
              <span>Features</span>
              <h2>The main features of the Reactoor</h2>
              <p>
                Using Reactoor's features and tools to design the best and most convenient websites
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".1s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-gift"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Free and Open-Source</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  One of the outstanding features of our framework is that it is free and open source and is being updated every moment                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".15s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-indent-decrease"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Management console</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  You can manage your project and design all kinds of classes and arms in the simplest way by using Reactor's framework CLI.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".2s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-layout"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Software engine</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Using the software template engine, you can get the best templates and use them in the project                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-database"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Database</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  One of the important features of the Reactoor framework is the flexibility of its Database section and you can develop it in any way
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-layers"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">MVC</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Mapping relationship to object is a set of methods to convert information stored in relational databases to common objects in object-oriented programming languages.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-archive"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">ORM</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  The most important and extensible framework of Reactoor is the object mapping interface part of converting database information into readable information
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-vector"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Routing</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  The main part of web networks is network routing, which with the Reactor framework, each path in the network must be defined in a specialized manner so that it can handle the desired requests and responses.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-plug"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Plugins</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Web programming plugins that make websites and applications expandable and flexible. You can get ready-made plugins and even customize them.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-display-alt"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">View compiler</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  You can design your front section using View Compiler, which is designed based on Laravel's view tools
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-reply"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Helpers</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Using the help of the framework, you can call the advanced classes with just one simple function and have all the features available in a simple way.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-hammer"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Kernel</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  The core of Reactor is based on converting each request into a packet and each packet into a response, and the responses are converted into network serials.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-pencil-alt"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Events</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Reactoor Events is a library that can be used to dispatch and intercept events. Moreover, it provides
                  advanced features such as filters and regex constraints.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-website-alt"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Http</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Reactoor HTTP is a library that provides an object-oriented representation for HTTP requests and
                  responses. The library was designed to be small, efficient, and easy to work with.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-hand"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Session</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Reactoor Session is a session manager library with support for multiple backend storages. It provides
                  developers with an API which allows them to handle session related information in a standardised way.                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-checkmark-circle"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Validation</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Reactoor Validation is a small and handy library that can be used to validate user input in a very
                  intuitive way.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-3 col-sm-6">
            <div class="ud-single-feature wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".25s">
              <div class="ud-feature-icon">
                <i class="lni lni-world"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="ud-feature-content">
                <h3 class="ud-feature-title">Intl</h3>
                <p class="ud-feature-desc">
                  Reactoor Intl is an internationalization library with support for translations and localized formats
                  for dates and numbers.                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
