                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Why should I use Reactor?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    Reactoor is one of the newest PHP frameworks and it may have errors that we are fixing and
                    developing day by day.
                    By taking advantage of the needs of a programmer, Reactor returns the best program to you in the form of defined outputs, and because of the layers of these requests, it is faster.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ud-single-faq wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".15s">
              <div class="accordion">
                <button
                  class="ud-faq-btn collapsed"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseTwo"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Why is it called a reactor?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    You see, the name of the reactor was the result of a simple kiss to thank for a chemistry exam. The reactor is the name of the programming team that designed the framework itself, under the supervision of Arshiamohamamdei. The reactor is named for this reason, because the reactor converts a raw material into, for example, isotopes and... It does and it takes energy from them. We made something like that to receive a raw material and turn it into something great, and the fact that Reactoor is written with an extra o is a personal preference.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ud-single-faq wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".2s">
              <div class="accordion">
                <button
                  class="ud-faq-btn collapsed"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseThree"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Why should we prefer this to other frameworks?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    You see, everything starts from a tool and from a weak activity. The Reactor framework is for those who want high productivity in low productivity and want the program to be completely designed for them, and Reactor is a very good way to learn PHP and other frameworks. php is like Laravel
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <div class="ud-single-faq wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".1s">
              <div class="accordion">
                <button
                  class="ud-faq-btn collapsed"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseFour"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Can we write very big projects?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    Yes, you can design any project with any volume of data with this framework
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ud-single-faq wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".15s">
              <div class="accordion">
                <button
                  class="ud-faq-btn collapsed"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseFive"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Can we use other platforms and languages ​​inside the framework?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    In addition to the separate compiler of the codes designed for the framework, you can compile html, you can also use the javasctip language and use other frameworks such as vue, nextjs, react,...
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ud-single-faq wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".2s">
              <div class="accordion">
                <button
                  class="ud-faq-btn collapsed"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseSix"
                >
                  <span class="icon flex-shrink-0">
                    <i class="lni lni-chevron-down"></i>
                  </span>
                  <span>Can we upload the project to the host?</span>
                </button>
                <div id="collapseSix" class="accordion-collapse collapse">
                  <div class="ud-faq-body">
                    Yes, you can upload and use all your projects on all types of hosts and any version of php or even servers because this framework can be used for any host and plan of any host, as long as php is installed on it.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
